            <section id="faq">
                <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
                <div class="faq-container">
                    <details class="faq-item">
                        <summary>What Is the Typical Turnaround Time for An Estimate?</summary>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <p>Turnaround times vary based on project complexity, but most residential and small commercial projects are completed within 8-16 Hours. We will provide a specific delivery date when you submit your plans.</p>
                        </div>
                    </details>
                    <details class="faq-item">
                        <summary>What Files Do I Need to Provide to Get Started?</summary>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <p>The best files to provide are PDF blueprints or plans. This includes architectural, structural, and MEP drawings. A clear scope of work is also essential for an accurate estimate.</p>
                        </div>
                    </details>
                    <details class="faq-item">
                        <summary>How Do You Ensure Pricing Is Accurate for My Region?</summary>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <p>We use up-to-date, zip-code-specific pricing databases like RSMeans and our own historical cost data. This ensures that all material and labor costs are adjusted for your specific project location.</p>
                        </div>
                    </details>
                    <details class="faq-item">
                        <summary>What Format Will I Receive the Final Estimate In?</summary>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <p>You will receive your estimate as a professional, easy-to-read PDF file. We also provide a detailed Excel spreadsheet that breaks down all quantities, materials, labor, and equipment costs for your convenience.</p>
                        </div>
                    </details>
                </div>
